<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: PL;">Annales Universitatis Paedagogicae Cracoviensis Studia Geographica is a continuation of a publication series known as the WSP Research and Teaching Yearbook – Geography Series, published since 1955. The Geography Series consisted of 18 volumes and covered the work of researchers at the Institute of Geography.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: PL;">Annales Universitatis Paedagogicae Cracoviensis Studia Geographica is a research journal featuring the latest research results in geography from a variety of institutions. The journal is focused on issues associated with cultural, social and economic variation across geographic space. Other issues of interest include the teaching of geography and geographic thought. </span><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-bidi-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-language: PL;">You are invited to submit papers to the Journal.</span></p>
