  'proofInstructions' => 
  array (
    'pl_PL' => 'The proofreading stage is intended to catch any errors in the galley\'s spelling, grammar, and formatting. More substantial changes cannot be made at this stage, unless discussed with the Section Editor. In Layout, click on VIEW PROOF to see the HTML, PDF, and other available file formats used in publishing this item. For Spelling and Grammar Errors Copy the problem word or groups of words and paste them into the Proofreading Corrections box with "CHANGE-TO" instructions to the editor as follows: 1. CHANGE... 	then the others 	TO... 	than the others  2. CHANGE... 	Malinowsky 	TO... 	Malinowski  For Formatting Errors Describe the location and nature of the problem in the Proofreading Corrections box after typing in the title "FORMATTING" as follows:  3. FORMATTING 	The numbers in Table 3 are not aligned in the third column.  4. FORMATTING 	The paragraph that begins "This last topic..." is not indented.',
